kernel-5.17-rt-15.x86_64
Only run build-all-kernels.sh

Right now the configuration is unfinished, it just the normal generic configuration.
More configuration and patches form the manjaro-rt kernel will be applied to this this kernel.

This is still experimental and unfinished but still somewhat useful.
DON'T USE THIS KERNEL UNTIL THE SECURITY PART ABOUT THE CONFIGURATION IS DONE: THEN I WILL REMOVE THIS TEXT

https://gitlab.manjaro.org/packages/community/realtime-kernels/linux517-rt

Also upgrade kernel-firmware from here https://mirrors.slackware.com/slackware/slackware64-current/slackware64/a/

Run first time to avoid conflicts with pkgs:
removepkg kernel-source kernel-generic kernel-modules kernel-headers

To install:
installpkg /tmp/output-x86_64-5.17-rt15/kernel*.txz

You might want to blacklist: /etc/slackpkg/blacklist

